<Article id="gdc-howto">
  <artheader>
    <Title>GDC HOWTO</Title>
    <AuthorGroup>
      &author.emk;
    </AuthorGroup>
  </artheader>
  
  <Para>The &gdc; compiler translates &dylan; programs into C programs,
  which it then compiles using &gcc;. Although &gdc; runs slowly, it
  produces fairly efficient code.</para>
  
  <Para>&gdc; was originally developed by CMU's &gwydprj;. The &gdmp;
  releases bugfixes and minor improvements for several platforms, including
  Linux.</para>

  <Sect1 id="installing-gdc">
    <Title>Installing GDC</TITLE>
    
    <Para>To install &gdc; on a Linux system using RPM, type:</para>
    
    <screen>
      <prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>ncftp &ftpdir;</userinput>
      <prompt>ncftp></prompt> <userinput>get gwydion-dylan*.rpm</userinput>
      <prompt>ncftp></prompt> <userinput>quit</userinput>
      <prompt>$</prompt> <userinput>su</userinput>
      <prompt>Password:</prompt> <userinput>secret!</userinput>
      <prompt>%</prompt> <userinput>rpm -Uvh gwydion-dylan*.rpm</userinput>
      <prompt>%</prompt> <userinput>exit</userinput>
    </screen>

    <para>On other systems, you can download the tarballs at &ftpdir; and
    install them in the usual fashion.</para>
  </sect1>
  
  <sect1 id="making-new-gdc-program">
    <title>Making a New GDC Program</title>
    
    <para>We need a Perl script to make a new program.</para>
  </sect1>
</article>
